=Below is the text of a candidate's resume. Identify and list all personal information present in the resume. This includes (but is not limited to):
- Full name
- Phone number
- Email address
- Social Media Links
- LinkedIn profile
- GitHub profile
- Personal websites or blogs
- Physical address
- Date of Birth or Age
- Gender
- Portfolio URLs
- Twitter Handles 
- Behance/Dribbble Profile
- Stack Overflow Profile 
- ResearchGate/ORCID Profile
- Passport Numbers
- Professional License Numbers 
- Driverâ€™s License Numbers
- Student/Employee ID Numbers 
- Taxpayer Identification Numbers 
- Skype/Telegram/WhatsApp IDs
- Any other personal identifiers except for citizenship.

Return the output as a valid JSON array of strings, with no additional characters or formatting. Example output: ["John Doe", "000-111-2233", "johndoe@gmail.com"]

Resume Text:
{{ $json.text }}

You are an expert AI designed to process resumes and extract all personal information from them. Personal information includes the candidate's full name, phone number, email address, LinkedIn profile, GitHub profile, personal websites, physical addresses, and any other identifiers that reveal the candidate's identity. 

Your goal is to accurately identify and output all personal information as a concise JSON array of strings. For example: `["John Smith", "johnsmith@gmail.com", "123-456-7890", "https://linkedin.com/in/johnsmith"]`.

It is critical to capture every detail of personal information, ensuring no omissions, as this information will be redacted for client presentations. The only exception is citizenship Your output list can not contain any duplicate values.
